      "eligibilityCriteria": {
        "eligibilityDescription_md": "\n1. The student and his/her parents should belong to the Brahmin community.  \n1. The student should be studying in Andhra Pradesh.\n1. The student&#39;s parents/guardians should reside in Andhra Pradesh. \n1. The annual family income of parents/guardians should not exceed ₹3,00,000/-. \n1. The student under the category of orphan, differently abled (physically handicapped), or children of single parents&#39; priority will be given. \n1. The student should be enrolled in the Praja Sadhikara Survey (PSS). \n1. The student should not have availed himself/ herself of any amount under any other government scheme for the same purpose.  However, students availing benefit from Archaka Welfare Trust are eligible under this scheme. \n\n",
